üîπ BASIC MCQs (10)
1. Information Security management mainly focuses on:
A. Hacking systems
B. Protecting information assets
C. Network routing
D. Software development

2. Which is the MOST important asset in an organization?
A. Hardware
B. Software
C. Information
D. Network

3. Human side of information security refers to:
A. Firewalls
B. Policies and procedures
C. People and behavior
D. Encryption

4. Which factor causes MOST security breaches?
A. Zero-day exploits
B. Weak encryption
C. Human error
D. Hardware failure

5. A threat is best defined as:
A. Existing vulnerability
B. Potential cause of harm
C. Security control
D. Security policy

6. An attack is:
A. A weakness
B. A policy violation
C. Exploitation of a vulnerability
D. A security asset

7. Which CIA triad component is MOST affected by insider threats?
A. Confidentiality
B. Integrity
C. Availability
D. All of the above

8. Social engineering attacks primarily target:
A. Network devices
B. Databases
C. Humans
D. Servers

9. Which is an example of a physical threat?
A. Phishing
B. Malware
C. Fire
D. SQL Injection

10. Security principles are designed to:
A. Increase profit
B. Reduce security risks
C. Improve UI
D. Speed up systems

